      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 13.011,
      "end": 15.535,
      "text": "Asop's fables, the fox and the grapes.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.337,
      "end": 27.68,
      "text": "A hungry fox saw some fine bunches of grapes hanging from a vine that was trained along a high trellis, and did his best to reach them by jumping as high as he could into the air.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 28.341,
      "end": 31.342,
      "text": "But it was all in vain, for they were just out of reach.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 32.022,
      "end": 41.325,
      "text": "So he gave up trying, and walked away with an air of dignity and unconcerned, remarking, I thought those grapes were ripe, but I see now they are quite sour.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 43.245,
      "end": 44.686,
      "text": "End of fox in the grapes",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
